reviewText: Nothing planned for a lazy day?  This is a great way to spend a few hours.  The movie is filled with all that you would expect to keep your interest - murder, romance, betrayal.  What more could you ask for?  And just as good the second time around!
summary: Good Movie for a Lazy Day
Title: Joy Fielding's The Other Woman

reviewText: THIS WAS ONE OF THE WORST MOVIES I HAVE EVER SEEN. THE STORYLINE IS SO STUPID! THE TITLE DEFINATELY DESCRIBES THE MOVIE; IT'S ABOUT A YOUNG MARRIED COUPLE WHO'SLIFE TURNS UPSIDE DOWN WHEN A NEW INTERN JOINS A LAW FIRM WHERE THE HUSBAND WORKS AND DOES EVERYTHING IN HER POWER TO RUIN THEIR MARRIAGE. IT SUCKS! DONT SEE IT YOU WILL BE DISGUSTED JUST AS I WAS. I WILL NEVER RECOMMEND THIS MOVIE TO A FRIEND; I VALUE MY FRIENDSHIP WITH THEM TOO MUCH!
Title: Joy Fielding's The Other Woman

reviewText: Great movie to watch on movie nights! Interesting twist. Glad I found it. I hope everyone enjoys them as much as I did!
Title: Joy Fielding's The Other Woman

reviewText: A successful news producer with a bright future, Jill Plumley (Josie Bisset) decides to forsake her career in favor of her new role--the devoted wife of her lawyer husband, David. One day, while at David's company party, a sexy young student named Nicole boldly tells Jill that she's going to steal her husband--a courageous yet ironic assertion, considering that 4 years ago, Jill stole David away from his ex-wife.Now that Jill is Mrs. David Plumley, could young Nicole be the other woman that Jill had been? Then, when David's boss is killed in his sleep and his wife confesses to the murder but claims self-defense, an overwhelmed Jill turns to old friend and fellow journalist Pete Henderson (Jason Priestley) to find out the truth. Based on the best-selling novel by Joy Fielding.It was also interesting seeing Jason Priestley who is best known as the foxy Brandon Walsh on BEVERLY HILLS 90210 and Josie Bissett whom is best known for her role as sexy designer Jane Mancini on MELROSE PLACE, co-star in this drama together, especially since MELROSE PLACE was a spinoff of BEVERLY HILLS, 90210.
Title: Joy Fielding's The Other Woman
